tasks.description:
The gateway's refdata and fees stores are empty when DATABASE_URL is not set because the in-memory store starts with zero data. Seed the default commodities and instruments from V17 migration into the in-memory store on startup.

Update `src/gateway/cmd/gateway/main.go`:

After creating the refdata store (whether PgStore or in-memory), seed the default data if the store is empty:

```go
// Seed default master data into in-memory store
if os.Getenv("DATABASE_URL") == "" {
    seedMasterData(refdataStore)
}

func seedMasterData(store refdata.Store) {
    // 6 commodities from V17 migration
    commodities := []refdata.CommodityInput{
        {ID: "WHT-HRW", Name: "Hard Red Winter Wheat", Category: "grain", Unit: "bushel"},
        {ID: "CRN-YEL", Name: "Yellow Corn", Category: "grain", Unit: "bushel"},
        {ID: "SBN-NO2", Name: "No.2 Soybeans", Category: "oilseed", Unit: "bushel"},
        {ID: "BRL-MALT", Name: "Malting Barley", Category: "grain", Unit: "bushel"},
        {ID: "CSH-RAW", Name: "Raw Cashmere", Category: "fiber", Unit: "kg"},
        {ID: "LVS-CATTLE", Name: "Live Cattle", Category: "livestock", Unit: "cwt"},
    }
    for _, c := range commodities {
        store.CreateCommodity(context.Background(), c)
    }

    // 6 instruments from V17 migration
    instruments := []refdata.InstrumentInput{
        {ID: "WHT-HRW-2026M07-UB", CommodityID: "WHT-HRW", Name: "HRW Wheat Jul 2026", ...},
        // ... all 6 instruments
    }
    for _, i := range instruments {
        store.CreateInstrument(context.Background(), i)
    }
}
```

Also seed default fee schedules and rules so `show fees` returns data.

Acceptance: `show commodities` via bot returns 6 commodities. `show instruments` via refdata returns 6 instruments.

The bot often returns raw JSON like `{"data": []}` which is confusing. Format all responses as human-readable text.

Update `src/gateway/internal/bot/executor.go`:

1. Replace raw JSON responses with formatted text for ALL handlers:
   - Empty lists: 'No commodities found. Use `create commodity` to add one.' (not `{"data": []}`)
   - Data lists: Format as numbered items, not raw JSON
   - Errors: Show friendly message with suggestion, not raw error JSON

2. Create helper formatters:
```go
func formatListResponse(entityName string, items []interface{}, fieldExtractor func(interface{}) string) string {
    if len(items) == 0 {
        return fmt.Sprintf("No %s found. Use `create %s` to add one.", entityName, strings.TrimSuffix(entityName, "s"))
    }
    lines := []string{fmt.Sprintf("%s (%d total):", entityName, len(items))}
    for i, item := range items {
        lines = append(lines, fmt.Sprintf("  %d. %s", i+1, fieldExtractor(item)))
    }
    return strings.Join(lines, "\n")
}
```

3. Improve specific handlers:
   - `show commodities` вЖТ 'рЯМЊ Commodities (6 total):\n  1. WHT-HRW вАФ Hard Red Winter Wheat (grain, bushel)\n  2. ...' 
   - `show instruments` вЖТ 'рЯУК Instruments (6 total):\n  1. WHT-HRW-2026M07-UB вАФ HRW Wheat Jul 2026\n  2. ...'
   - `show participants` вЖТ 'рЯС• Participants (3 total):\n  1. farmer1@demo вАФ APPROVED\n  2. ...'
   - Empty results вЖТ 'No [entity] found. Use `create [entity]` to add one.'

Acceptance: No raw JSON in bot responses. All data formatted as readable text.
